description:
The Woocommerce module will create Items on-the-fly in two forms:

 - **Standard** - order items without attributes will be created as normal Items, there is no additional configuration necessary
 - **Variants** - order items with attributes **must** have Item templates with an Item Code that matches the Woocommerce `sku`, and with Item Attributes that match those sent by Woocommerce. The Woocommerce Settings Attribute Key Prefix will be stripped from the `key` and the result used as the Item Attribute Name. The `value` must either be a number, or be a human-readable string equivalent and a code value separated by an underscore, some examples:

`'key': 'prefix_width', 'value': '123.4'` - numeric attribute

`'key': 'prefix_colour', 'value': 'pale_blue_1234'` - numeric attribute

`'key': 'prefix_colour', 'value': 'bright_red_RED'` - non-numeric attribute
name: Items
title: Configure Item Templates
